data.title: Fifteen 3D (20000 followers)
data.description:
It's a fairly simple 3D engine but does allow multiple models to be created and instantiated as many times as required. For example, you could create one house model and add it to your world as many times as you wanted to. It also has basics such as directional lighting, hidden surface removal, etc. Maybe I'll optimise it and use it for something else in the future. Probably I won't.

"Fastest Quad fill v1.3" by ggenije2

data.instructions:
Read this if you have any questions
————————————————
RELOAD THE GAME IF THERE ARE QUESTION MARKS
————————————————
-> Controlls
a,d             left or right
space        jump
w               sprint
s                sneak

e                open your inventory
q                drop the item held in your hand
c                switch to "freecam" mode (hold)
                  -> v to focus on your opponents bed
                  -> b to focus on your own bed
leftclick      to use the item held in your hand. You can                            
                 only hit your opponent using your sword
scroll         to select the hotbar slot
leftclick      to open the shop without holding a sword in your hand

Click the arrows in the shop to switch the shop page. This is what you can find on the shop pages:
-> different blocks
-> armor
-> tools and weapons 
-> explosives
-> potions
-> special items

-> haste effect
-> strength effect
-> healpool in your base

-> How to play
Collect resources in the different spawners. Buy useful items or improvements in the two shops. Protect your bed by surrounding it with sturdy blocks and attack your opponent. To win you have to destroy his bed and then defeat him. As long as the bed is still standing, you will respawn again after 5 seconds.
It is also possible to compete against friends. There is also possible to play vs s bot. He plays tactically. Adjust the difficulty and try to achieve a best time if you want to make it particularly difficult.

               All bugs can be fixed by reloading.               
                             -- Buttons --
                    Button 1: Changes Music
                    Button 2: Adjust volume
                      Button 3: Caps Lock
                     Button 4: Copy Paste 

                            -- Help --
                Rule #1) Type 5 Letters.
               Rule #2) Type any number.
 Rule #3) Press [Enter] while typing any letter or tap the  Caps Lock button on the side. You will need to turn it                                                    
                        off when you are done. 
          Rule #4) Type one of these: !@#$%^&*()
Rule #5) Carefully, type out numbers until they add up                  
                                     to 25.
Rule #6) Type any month. I seriously recommend using        
       June, as it has no Roman numerals in it.

  Rule #9) Type in the correct amount of Roman
